author: GameTimePA.com report
title: CROSS COUNTRY: Thursday's roundup
text:
GameTimePA.com report Posted: 10/01/2015 11:06:32 PM EDT 
GREENCASTLE, SHIPPENSBURG SPLIT >> Greencastle-Antrim picked up a dominating Mid Penn Colonial Division boys cross country victory, but it was Shippensburg that won the girls race. 
The Blue Devils won the boys race, 16-47, while Ship girls came out on top, 24-33. 
Greencastle-Antrim (5-0, 5-0 MPC) took the top four spots in the boys race. Daniel Salazar and Andrew Johnson both posted times of 17:28 to take the top two spots. Shippensburg's fastest boy was Hunter Kent who placed fifth in 18:14. 
Greencastle's Madison Hurley won the girls race in 19:58, but the Lady Hounds claimed six of the top 10 spots. Ava Franklin led Ship in second place, clocking in at 21:35. BOYS Greencastle 16, Shippensburg 47 
1.Daniel Salazar (GA) 17:28, 2.Andrew Johnson (GA) 17:28, 3.Billie Schemel (GA) 17:47, 4.Dylan Neikirk (GA) 18:05, 5.Hunter Kent (S) 18:14, 6.Dylan Hummer (GA) 18:28, 7.Brock Widder (GA) 18:58, 8.Joe Eberhardt (GA) 19:21, 9.Hayden Rhinehart (S) 19:21, 10.Luke Norris (GA) 19:29. GIRLS Shippensburg 24, Greencastle 33 
1.Madison Hurley (GA) 19:58, 2.Ava Franklin (S) 21:35, 3.Coramina Cogan (GA) 22:19, 4.Madeline Goodhart (S) 23:23, 5.Audrey Goates (S) 23:27, 6.Megan Pomeroy (S) 23:30, 7.Catherine C-Brown (S) 23:30, 8.Abriana Cain (GA) 23:48, 9.Hannah Goldbach (GA) 24:09, 10.Lauren Taylor (S) 24:48. Advertisement
